77
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:29,820
I spent years at the CIA after leaving NSA and ODNI, where I was basically the CTO of the U.S. intelligence community, the whole thing.

78
00:05:29,820 --> 00:05:40,720
And I was an analyst for a particular target and was trained in analytic tradecraft, which is basically the scientific method.

79
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:43,880
And we call it the method of competing hypothesis.

80
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:51,580
When we see a phenomena or an event, we say, what are all the different hypotheses for what could be driving this?

81
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:56,880
And then we go and we look for evidence that would support or contradict each of those.

82
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:08,980
And at the end, we weigh it and come out with an assessment with the probability of what we think is the most likely of all of those with some confidence.

83
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:20,380
And so, for example, in Iran, you have the Iran group at the different agencies doing that now saying, OK, Iranians have a nuclear program.

84
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:27,200
What is our best guess and at what probability about where they are in that program and what their intent is?

85
00:06:28,060 --> 00:06:29,000
Right. So that's an example.

86
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:32,760
So with the UFOs, UAPs, we did the same.

87
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,300
We said, OK, here are the reporting.

88
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:38,460
