104
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:17,320
I mean, we always assume if it's from Earth that it has to be human.

105
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:21,140
Well, what we look at is the old Sherlock Holmes thing.

106
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:22,560
What isn't impossible?

107
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:34,020
And we'll get into this more, but at CIA, we used to have a saying, an analyst that says, do not look for your keys under the lamppost.

108
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:36,460
Right.

109
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,920
Don't look only where you can see.

110
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:47,820
So if you're not seeing something, it's probably because you don't know where else to look.

111
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:54,740
So one thing we used to do is say, what do we know or think we know?

112
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,640
What can we see and not see?

113
00:08:56,980 --> 00:09:02,520
