02:02:37,680 --> 02:03:07,680
So you continue on the search. You build up these kind of layers of knowledge, but then the questions grow exponentially more. And I think it really touches on the idea with the phenomenon that, that this book and the movie Arrival also kind of, it does a good job of this. It's weirder than you can think. And it's not only weirder than you can think. And I think there's an Arthur C. Clarke quote about this. It's weirder than you can think. It's weirder than you can think.

